    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is offset by the strong quantitative agreement across all three QoIs (all E/uval < 1.96, all percent differences < 10%) and the use of N=11 constructs across two independent laboratories. The overall credibility evidence is judged sufficient to support a Medium assurance level for this Class II device regulatory submission. The assessment team accepts the model for the stated intended use.",
